 <section class="card rights-panel">
-<h2>Why recordings are handled separately</h2>
-<p>An ancient or public-domain hymn and a modern studio recording are different rights objects. This release therefore provides browser-based Tamil read-aloud for verified texts and keeps every commercial or modern recording out until ownership or an explicit licence is documented.</p>
-<p><strong>Available now:</strong> Kanda Sashti Kavasam reviewed opening extract, Kanda Gayatri and Saravanabhava Mantra. The ten verified Thiruppugazh Volume 1 pages also have read-aloud controls.</p>
+<h2>Real functionality—no simulated audio</h2>
+<p>This player reads verified Tamil text through the speech voice installed on the visitor’s device. It does not display a fake duration, fake waveform, false “Hi-Fi” badge or pretend that a modern studio recording is available.</p>
+<p><strong>Current verified queue:</strong> four mantra or Kavasam records plus ten Thiruppugazh songs. No playback starts automatically.</p>
